 Gov. Rochas Okorocha of Imo has reiterated that the political future of the Igbo race can only be guaranteed in the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC. January 21, 2017 In "News" Owerri—As reactions continued to trail the judgment of the Supreme Court on Imo gubernatorial election, nine lawmakers of Imo State House of Assembly, yesterday, defected to All Progressives Congress, APC, to join the government of Senator Hope Uzodinma,  increasing the number of APC lawmakers  to 10. January 22, 2020 In "Politics" Twenty Imo lawmakers on the platform of All Progressives Congress, APC, including the Speaker, Paul Emeziem, on Monday, said they had finalised plans to recommend the expulsion of Senator Ifeanyi Araraume to the national leadership and state executive of the party. December 7, 2020 In "Politics"